theorem Topology.P3_union_of_dense_right
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 A → Dense B → Topology.P3 (A ∪ B) := by
  intro hP3A hDenseB
  dsimp [Topology.P3] at hP3A ⊢
  intro x hx
  cases hx with
  | inl hxA =>
      -- Use `P3` for `A` and monotonicity of `interior ∘ closure`.
      have hxIntA : x ∈ interior (closure A) := hP3A hxA
      have hsubset : interior (closure A) ⊆ interior (closure (A ∪ B)) := by
        apply interior_mono
        have : closure A ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) := by
          apply closure_mono
          intro y hy
          exact Or.inl hy
        exact this
      exact hsubset hxIntA
  | inr _hxB =>
      -- Density of `B` forces `closure (A ∪ B)` to be the whole space.
      have hclosureB : closure B = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
        simpa using hDenseB.closure_eq
      have hclosureUnion : closure (A ∪ B) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
        apply Set.Subset.antisymm
        · intro y hy; simp
        · intro y _
          have hyB : y ∈ closure B := by
            have : y ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by simp
            simpa [hclosureB] using this
          have hsubset : closure B ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) := by
            apply closure_mono
            intro z hz
            exact Or.inr hz
          exact hsubset hyB
      have hIntUniv : interior (closure (A ∪ B)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
        simpa [hclosureUnion, interior_univ]
      have : x ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by simp
      simpa [hIntUniv] using this

theorem Topology.interior_closure_eq_univ_of_dense_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (h : Dense (interior A)) :
    interior (closure A) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  -- First, record that the closure of `interior A` is the whole space.
  have h_closure : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa using h.closure_eq
  -- Prove the desired equality by showing each inclusion.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    -- The forward inclusion is immediate.
    intro _ _
    simp
  ·
    -- For the reverse inclusion, start with an arbitrary point `x : X`.
    intro x _
    -- Because `closure (interior A) = univ`, its interior is also `univ`,
    -- so `x` certainly lies in that interior.
    have hx₁ : x ∈ interior (closure (interior A)) := by
      simpa [h_closure, interior_univ] using (by
        have : x ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
          simp
        exact this)
    -- Monotonicity of `interior` composed with `closure` upgrades the membership.
    have hx₂ :
        interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
      apply interior_mono
      have : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A :=
        closure_mono (interior_subset : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ A)
      exact this
    exact hx₂ hx₁

theorem Topology.P3_of_dense {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : Dense A) : Topology.P3 A := by
  -- `Dense A` gives `closure A = univ`.
  have hclosure : closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa using hA.closure_eq
  -- Apply the existing lemma that turns this equality into `P3`.
  simpa using Topology.P3_of_closure_eq_univ (A := A) hclosure

theorem Topology.interior_closure_eq_of_isClosed_of_P3
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed A) (hP3 : Topology.P3 A) :
    interior (closure A) = A := by
  -- From `P3` and closedness we get that `A` is open.
  have hOpen : IsOpen A :=
    (Topology.isOpen_of_P3_of_isClosed (A := A) hA_closed) hP3
  -- The interior of an open set is itself.
  have hInt : interior A = A := hOpen.interior_eq
  -- The closure of a closed set is itself.
  have hCl : closure A = A := hA_closed.closure_eq
  -- Combine the two equalities.
  simpa [hCl, hInt]
